% Failed :assign by (T4) consistency hook (BETA1 spec section 2.3.6 + 3.2.3).
% A query that adds an arithmetic constraint reaches a paused step at
% which `_LeftConstraints = [X > 5]` is visible. Attempting
% `:assign ?X := 3.` would make the candidate substitution inconsistent
% with the accumulated constraint (3 > 5 is false). The runtime aborts
% the assign with "*** :assign error: inconsistent with arithmetic
% constraints for 'X'" and restores the snapshot. No subsequent fact
% can satisfy the original goal (X > 5 with X unbound has no ground
% witness reachable through search), so the query ultimately fails.
type p (nat -> o).
